  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read playbook-architecture.md">Focus on: data model (sprk_analysisaction + sprk_actiontype shape), ActionType dispatch mechanism, canvas design (Designer-vs-deploy interaction)</step>
    <step order="2" name="Read scope-model-index.json">Focus on: actions[] section (existing JPS-backed actions), models[] section (for understanding completion model selection), modelSelectionRules[]</step>
    <step order="3" name="Read JPS-AUTHORING-GUIDE.md">Focus on: schema reference, $ref / $choices patterns, sprk_actiontype field semantics</step>
    <step order="4" name="Read jps-action-create + jps-playbook-design skill bodies">Note their conventions (frontmatter, exemplars, workflow steps) to ensure Wave B tasks 002+ invoke them correctly</step>
    <step order="5" name="Synthesize findings vs D-01 Q1+Q2+Q3">Record under D-01 §3 — replace each question with "Resolved per [doc citation]: [finding]"</step>
    <step order="6" name="Validate that the re-scoped Wave B remains viable">If findings significantly contradict path-b assumptions (e.g., canvas Designer cannot be prevented from clobbering), update D-01 §4 with the corrected sequence + re-present to owner</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
